    {
      "id": "1ldstqqon",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "<p>17 mg of a hydrocarbon (M.F. $$\\mathrm{C_{10}H_{16}}$$) takes up 8.40 mL of the H$$_2$$ gas measured at 0$$^\\circ$$C and 760 mm of Hg. Ozonolysis of the same hydrocarbon yields</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldt1rxxw/88b702e1-8d9c-4bf5-b704-beed3273c33e/1ae96540-a63e-11ed-8e98-03be028140e9/file-1ldt1rxxx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldt1rxxw/88b702e1-8d9c-4bf5-b704-beed3273c33e/1ae96540-a63e-11ed-8e98-03be028140e9/file-1ldt1rxxx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 29th January Morning Shift Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 74 English\"></p>\n<p>The number of double bond/s present in the hydrocarbon is ___________.</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "reaction-of-alkenes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Moles of hydrocarbon $=\\frac{17 \\times 10^{-3}}{136}=1.25 \\times 10^{-4}$\n<br/><br/>\nMole of $\\mathrm{H}_{2}$ gas\n<br/><br/>\n$\\Rightarrow 1 \\times \\frac{8.40}{1000}=\\mathrm{n} \\times 0.0821 \\times 273$\n<br/><br/>\n$\\Rightarrow \\mathrm{n}=3.75 \\times 10^{-4}$\n<br/><br/>\nHydrogen molecule used for 1 molecule of hydrocarbon is 3\n<br/><br/>\n$=\\frac{3.75 \\times 10^{-4}}{1.25 \\times 10^{-4}}=3$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "dfPoS0b0mi8tnOtL",
      "questionNumber": 8,
      "questionText": "The main product of the following reaction is \n<br><br>$$\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,$$ $${C_6}{H_5}C{H_2}CH\\left( {OH} \\right)CH{\\left( {C{H_3}} \\right)_2}\\buildrel {conc.{H_2}S{O_4}} \\over\n \\longrightarrow \\,?$$ ",
